    <p>This de­bate was like the coun­try: Ev­ery­body’s talk­ing. No­body’s lis­ten­ing. Noth­ing is learnt. It’s a mess.</p>
    <p>MR MIKE ALLEN, of Ax­ios news web­site.</p>
    <p>DIS­COUR­AG­ING AND DE­PRESS­ING</p>
    <p>That was the most dis­cour­ag­ing, most de­press­ing, most trou­bling 90 min­utes I can re­call. If you are not wor­ried about the fu­ture of this coun­try, you were not watch­ing.</p>
    <p>DR RICHARD HAASS, pres­i­dent of the Coun­cil on For­eign Re­la­tions, a US think-tank</p>
    <p>That was a hot mess, in­side a dump­ster fire, in­side a train wreck... The Amer­i­can peo­ple lost.</p>
    <p>CNN’S JAKE TAP­PER</p>
    <p>LOW POINT</p>
    <p>A low point in Amer­i­can po­lit­i­cal dis­course.</p>
